      • hasBeenAnalyzed

        boolean hasBeenAnalyzed()
        Some DBMS implementations will have rows in the system tables for indexes and/or histograms that have not been analyzed. Others will not. Those that have not been analyzed are of interest as their presence could be a problem.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the Object corresponds to an index or histogram that has been analyzed.
